    "Reporting guidelines may be specific to the unique needs of a single clinical specialty or intended to be more general in nature.",
    "In addition, due to the highly dynamic nature of AI research, these guidelines require frequent reassessment to safeguard against obsolescence.",
    "As a consequence of the breadth of stakeholders involved in the development and regulation of medical AI, including government organizations, academic institutions, publishers and corporations, a multitude of reporting guidelines have arisen.",
    "The repercussion of this is a notable lack of clarity for researchers as to which guidelines to follow, uncertainty whether or not guidelines exist for their specific domain of research, and whether or not reporting standards can be expected to be enforced by publishers of mainstream academic journals.",
